rComments: Clear and direct with what she expects in the class. Does examples and makes sure everybody understands which is great! Sometimes difficult to hear but other than that I really recommend her.

Always prepared and easy to understand. For a morning class, the subject matter kept me awake. Definitely recommend this class. She expresses the subject matter so well I didn't even buy the textbook and got an A on everything!

why is such an intersting class taught by such a boring teacher!! pointless to go to class, tests based on the readings from the book, the textbook is your bible, slides are so pointless you don't need them or her teacher cuz she repeats what says in the book, bad choice of TAs.

Seems to get a little confused by her own material, and doesn't always convey the lectures effectively, but overall a good prof. Easy class. No surprises on the exams. I skipped the majority of the classes and still came out on top. Some of the material gets a bit tricky, but the textbook she uses is good reference material.

she was pretty good...easy. Notes and lectures were clear and so was the mid term and exam...Everything in the notes or text was in the exams...she was nice, but a litle opinionated but overall a good prof

People seem to love this prof, but I find her to be very opinionated when it comes to subjective questions on her midterms. We are forced to take one side (hers) on the questions, and it really isn't fair. That being said, her class is easy, but she will purposefully word things strangely on the tests just to mess you up.

A very good prof, on the whole. Explained the material well, was extremely friendly and approachable, made the course structure clear. At times, was a little too mild to make the material seem interesting, but did a great job teaching.

Awesome prof.  Cheap course notes and text on reserve.  I wonder if the content was just that easy or she was that good a prof but I'm probably going to get an A+.  Multiple-choice tests.  Really nice!
Excellent examples, and thorough coverage of material.  Always willing to help out new students.

Very clear and thorough, she goes through everything carefully to make sure everyone understands.  Tests are straightforward and fair. She has a fun sense of humour and her classes are well organised and enjoyable.
